---
---

<section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-neutral-50 border-y border-neutral-100">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center">
      <p class="text-k9-orange font-semibold text-sm tracking-wide uppercase mb-3">Sound familiar?</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold text-neutral-900 leading-tight">
        You love your dog. But right now,<br class="hidden sm:block" /> every walk feels like a battle.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 sm:mt-12 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
      {[
        "You can't walk your dog without dreading every other dog or person you see",
        "Your puppy is out of control and you don't know what you're doing wrong",
        "You've tried other trainers and nothing has stuck",
        "You're embarrassed to have people over because of how your dog behaves",
        "You've watched every YouTube video — it works for 2 days then goes back to normal",
        "You've stopped taking your dog to the park entirely",
      ].map((pain) => (
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-neutral-200/60">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126zM12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008z" />
          </svg>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">{pain}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 sm:p-8 border border-neutral-200/60">
      <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
        You've already tried everything.
      </h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        The YouTube videos. The treats. The "positive-only" trainer who told you to just redirect. The puppy class that didn't cover anything past "sit." You've spent months — maybe years — trying to fix this yourself.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
        And every time, it works for a few days. Then your dog goes right back to lunging, ignoring you, or losing it every time someone walks past.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 text-center">
      <h3 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-extrabold text-neutral-900 mb-4">
        Your dog isn't broken. The approach is.
      </h3>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        K9 Academy uses a balanced training approach — including e-collar protocols most Toronto trainers refuse to touch — that addresses the root cause, not just the symptoms.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <a
          href="#services"
          class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-white text-neutral-900 text-sm font-semibold rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 hover:border-neutral-300 hover:shadow-sm transition-all"
        >
          See Our Programs
          <svg class="ml-2 w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 13.5L12 21m0 0l-7.5-7.5M12 21V3" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
